---
// HowItWorks — 3-step overview inspired by Teton’s 01/02/03 layout
---
<section class="brutalist-section">
  <div class="brutalist-container">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="brutalist-heading text-4xl md:text-6xl mb-4">How it works</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl">One platform that simulates difficult scenarios, detects bias, and turns every session into measurable progress.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-6 bg-gray-900/40">
        <div class="text-6xl font-semibold text-accent/90 leading-none mb-4">01</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Point of care</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Run high‑risk conversations safely. No real patients, no clinical exposure required.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-6 bg-gray-900/40">
        <div class="text-6xl font-semibold text-accent/90 leading-none mb-4">02</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">In‑session guidance</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Bias and empathy cues nudge trainees toward better prompts and responses.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-6 bg-gray-900/40">
        <div class="text-6xl font-semibold text-accent/90 leading-none mb-4">03</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Program‑level insight</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Debriefs and metrics benchmark cohorts, highlight risk, and document competency.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

